<TITLE> Defence policy being drafted: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24.com)A national defence policy is being formulated, planning minister AK Khandakar told the House on Tuesday. The retired air vice marshal said the policy, a first for Bangladesh, would be finalised after proper review at all levels. He also informed the house that 86 members of the armed forces had died during Bangladesh's 20 years in the UN's peace missions, from 1989-2009. He also said compensation was paid to the families of 69 of the dead peacekeepers. Compensation for the rest of the families was under process. The state minister for liberation war affairs informed the house that the government has a plan to raise the freedom fighters allowance. He said 100,000 freedom fighters were now receiving the allowance of Tk 900 a month. bdnew
